Quote: VERVAIN (<i>Verbena officinalis </i>), also called blue top, griffin weed, and missionary weed, is a slender tough-stemmed perenial 1 to 2 ft. high, with a few opposite rough, cleft leaves, and small lilac flowers, ... It is becoming very common in the country from Wairoa to Gisborne
